\begin_layout Standard

The real part of the barriers, associated with the discrete transition states, are parameterized as a function of the quadrupole deformation using smoothly joined parabolas
\begin_inset Formula \begin{equation}
V_{i}(\beta)=E_{fi}+(-1)^{i}\frac{1}{2}\mu\hbar^{2}\omega_{i}^{2}(\beta-\beta_{i})^{2},\label{vfund0}\end{equation}
\end_inset

 where 
\begin_inset Formula $i=1$
\end_inset

 for a single barrier, runs from 1 to 3 for a two-humped barrier, and from 1 to 5 for a three-humped one. The energies 
\begin_inset Formula $E_{fi}$
\end_inset

