\begin_inset Formula $\gamma$
\end_inset

-transitions. The total number of levels with unique spin is 12956, and there are an additional 8708 levels with uncertain spin or parity assignment.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

The level schemes were analyzed using constant temperature fits to the cumulative plots for all nuclei with at least 30 known levels in order to determine the cut-off energy (E
\begin_inset Formula $_{{max}}$
\end_inset

) and the corresponding cumulative number of levels (N
\begin_inset Formula $_{{max}}$
\end_inset

) up to which schemes can be assumed complete and suitable for reaction calculations. These results were extended to cover all remaining nuclei using the nuclear temperature inferred from the above analysis. The energy U
\begin_inset Formula $_{{c}}$
\end_inset

, corresponding to the highest level with known and unique spin and parity assignment in the ENSDF, was subsequently determined for all nuclei.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

For the purpose of reaction calculations the library was completed by estimating data missing in the basic ENSDF set:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

unique spins and parities for all levels below the cutoff energy E
\begin_inset Formula $_{{max}}$
\end_inset

 were generated by (i) analyzing 
\begin_inset Formula $\gamma$
\end_inset

-transitions (3560), (ii) drawing from the assumed spin distribution (3551), and (iii) selecting from the list suggested in ENSDF (6280). 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

21595 Internal Conversion Coefficients (ICC) for electromagnetic transitions available in the original ENSDF data set were supplemented with 92634 ICCs calculated by cubic spline interpolation of values tabulated by Hager and Seltzer for the K, L, and M shells and by Dragoun, Plajner, and Schmetzler for the N+O+... shells. 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

if ENSDF reported de-exciting transitions from a level but did not specify the decay modes, 100% electromagnetic decay was assigned to the level. If other decay modes were indicated, the percentage of the electromagnetic mode was obtained from the available information on the decay modes and flagged by %IT or %G in the data files. 
\end_layout

