\begin_layout Subsection

"runE" sequence (Run EMPIRE)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

The runE script sets up the environment for a new EMPIRE calculation and cleans-up the directories before launching a new EMPIRE calculation. More specifically, the following tasks are performed:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

The EMPIREDIR environment variable is set, if necessary (see section 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "sec:EMPIREDIR"

\end_inset

 for more information)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

Unnecessary files from a previous run are deleted.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

Locally modified files containing input parameters are retrieved.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

EMPIRE is executed; case-related files are renamed as appropriate.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

If the experimental data in computational C4 format are not available, they are generated from the EXFOR file, if present. 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

The "project name" is defined at this step. Usually this identifies the nuclide that is being processed (e.g. mn55, w182, u235, etc.). The project name is used in the filenames and is implied in the sections below whenever the "*" appears in the filename.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection

"format" sequence
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

The following tasks are performed:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

EMPEND is executed to produce an ENDF file from the "short" EMPIRE output (with extension *.OUT). The input file for EMPEND is generated within the script. The output file *-e.endf is produced. 
