The resonance file (MF=2) that is generated for files with incident neutrons is by no means a realistic cross section representation. It is given for completeness, when no information on the resonances (other than from the systematics is available). The code places resonances spaced uniformly around the thermal value according to the given average level spacing. The neutron width is defined from the S0 strength function and the gamma-widths are the average gamma widths. The assigned resonance formalism is the Multi-level Breit-Wigner formalism with energy-dependent scattering radius. 
