\emph on
inp
\emph default
) that requires running the 
\emph on
clean
\emph default
 script (see above). Calculation times for such runs are very short. 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

If the ENDF option is selected, the incident energies should be in increasing order. 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

Log files 
\emph on
*.war, *.x42c4_errs
\emph default
 and 
\emph on
empend.log
\emph default
 should be checked for possible warnings and error messages. 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

Irregularities in the excitation functions such as (n,2n) or (n,p) are usually due to improper level density
